{
  "video_id": "PrK0CifulU0",
  "title": "Hamilton vs. Madison and the birth of American partisanship | Noah Feldman",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12835.0,
      "end_time": 16116.0,
      "text": "If you&#39;ve been thinking about US politics"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 16140.0,
      "end_time": 19571.0,
      "text": "and trying to make sense of it for the last year or so,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 20627.0,
      "end_time": 24285.0,
      "text": "you might have hit on something like the following three propositions:"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 24866.0,
      "end_time": 29556.0,
      "text": "one, US partisanship has never been so bad before;"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 31320.0,
      "end_time": 32588.0,
      "text": "two,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 32612.000000000004,
      "end_time": 36386.0,
      "text": "for the first time, it&#39;s geographically spatialized --"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 36410.0,
      "end_time": 40357.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re divided between the coasts, which want to look outwards,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 40381.0,
      "end_time": 43498.0,
      "text": "and the center of the country, which wants to look inwards;"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 43522.0,
      "end_time": 44801.0,
      "text": "and third,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 44825.0,
      "end_time": 47341.0,
      "text": "there&#39;s nothing we can do about it."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 49500.0,
      "end_time": 52730.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m here to today to say that all three of these propositions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 52755.0,
      "end_time": 54759.0,
      "text": "all of which sound reasonable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 54783.0,
      "end_time": 55997.0,
      "text": "are not true."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 56895.0,
      "end_time": 58960.0,
      "text": "In fact,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 58120.0,
      "end_time": 61440.0,
      "text": "our US partisanship goes all the way back"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 61465.0,
      "end_time": 63997.0,
      "text": "to the very beginning of the republic."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 65247.0,
      "end_time": 70330.0,
      "text": "It was geographically spatialized in almost eerily the same way"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 70354.0,
      "end_time": 71647.0,
      "text": "that it is today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 71671.0,
      "end_time": 74480.0,
      "text": "and it often has been throughout US history."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 75642.0,
      "end_time": 76792.0,
      "text": "And last,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 76816.0,
      "end_time": 79190.0,
      "text": "and by far most importantly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 79214.0,
      "end_time": 83515.0,
      "text": "we actually have an extraordinary mechanism"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 83540.0,
      "end_time": 88678.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s designed to help us manage factional disagreement and partisanship."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 89433.0,
      "end_time": 92242.0,
      "text": "That technology is the Constitution."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 93810.0,
      "end_time": 98975.0,
      "text": "And this is an evolving, subtly, supplely designed entity"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 98999.0,
      "end_time": 100539.0,
      "text": "that has the specific purpose"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 100563.0,
      "end_time": 104480.0,
      "text": "of teaching us how to manage factional disagreement"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 104720.0,
      "end_time": 105966.0,
      "text": "where it&#39;s possible to do that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 105990.0,
      "end_time": 109670.0,
      "text": "and giving us techniques for overcoming that disagreement"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 109695.0,
      "end_time": 111600.0,
      "text": "when that&#39;s possible."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 111771.0,
      "end_time": 114282.0,
      "text": "Now, in order to tell you the story,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 114306.0,
      "end_time": 118570.0,
      "text": "I want to go back to a pivotal moment in US history,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 118594.0,
      "end_time": 119749.0,
      "text": "and that is the moment"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 119773.0,
      "end_time": 123320.0,
      "text": "when factional disagreement and partisanship was born."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 123797.0,
      "end_time": 125616.0,
      "text": "There actually was a birth moment --"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 125640.0,
      "end_time": 128851.0,
      "text": "a moment in US history when partisanship snapped into place."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 130601.0,
      "end_time": 135619.0,
      "text": "The person who&#39;s at the core of that story is James Madison."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 136120.0,
      "end_time": 138741.0,
      "text": "And at the moment that this began,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 138765.0,
      "end_time": 141250.0,
      "text": "James Madison was riding high."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 142000.0,
      "end_time": 146471.0,
      "text": "He himself was the Einstein of not only the US Constitution,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 146495.0,
      "end_time": 148960.0,
      "text": "but of constitutional thought more globally,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 148984.0,
      "end_time": 151130.0,
      "text": "and, to give him his due,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 151370.0,
      "end_time": 152242.0,
      "text": "he knew it."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 153145.0,
      "end_time": 156239.0,
      "text": "In a period of time of just three years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 156263.0,
      "end_time": 158621.0,
      "text": "from 1785 to 1788,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 158645.0,
      "end_time": 165440.0,
      "text": "he had conceived, theorized, designed, passed and gotten ratified"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 165680.0,
      "end_time": 166609.0,
      "text": "the US Constitution."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 166633.0,
      "end_time": 168870.0,
      "text": "And just to give you some sense of the enormity"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 168894.0,
      "end_time": 170966.0,
      "text": "of what that accomplishment actually was,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 170990.0,
      "end_time": 173885.0,
      "text": "although Madison couldn&#39;t have known it at the time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 173909.0,
      "end_time": 179220.0,
      "text": "today that same constitutional technology that he invented is still in use"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 179244.0,
      "end_time": 180925.0,
      "text": "not only in the US,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 180949.0,
      "end_time": 182433.0,
      "text": "but, 230 years later,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 182457.0,
      "end_time": 184799.0,
      "text": "in places like Canada,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 184824.0,
      "end_time": 186644.0,
      "text": "India,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 186668.0,
      "end_time": 188191.0,
      "text": "South Africa,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 188215.0,
      "end_time": 189813.0,
      "text": "Brazil."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 189837.0,
      "end_time": 192716.0,
      "text": "So in an extraordinary range of contexts all over the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 192741.0,
      "end_time": 194821.0,
      "text": "this technology is still the dominant,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 194845.0,
      "end_time": 198103.0,
      "text": "most used, most effective technology to manage governance."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 199816.0,
      "end_time": 201757.0,
      "text": "In that moment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 201781.0,
      "end_time": 205353.0,
      "text": "Madison believed that, having solved this problem,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 205377.0,
      "end_time": 206992.0,
      "text": "the country would run smoothly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 207160.0,
      "end_time": 208823.0,
      "text": "and that he had designed a technology"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 208848.0,
      "end_time": 211894.0,
      "text": "that would minimize the results of factions"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 211918.0,
      "end_time": 214900.0,
      "text": "so there would be no political parties."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 214114.0,
      "end_time": 216623.0,
      "text": "Remarkably, he thought he had designed a constitution"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 216647.0,
      "end_time": 218346.0,
      "text": "that was against political parties"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 218370.0,
      "end_time": 220296.0,
      "text": "and would make them unnecessary."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 220320.0,
      "end_time": 222226.0,
      "text": "He had gotten an enormous degree of help"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 222250.0,
      "end_time": 226930.0,
      "text": "in the final marketing phase of his constitutional project"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 226117.0,
      "end_time": 229185.0,
      "text": "from a man you may have heard of, called Alexander Hamilton."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 230313.0,
      "end_time": 233571.0,
      "text": "Now, Hamilton was everything Madison was not."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 234134.0,
      "end_time": 238524.0,
      "text": "He was passionate, where Madison was restrained."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 238549.0,
      "end_time": 240397.0,
      "text": "He was pansexual,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 240421.0,
      "end_time": 243261.0,
      "text": "where Madison didn&#39;t speak to a woman expect for once"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 243285.0,
      "end_time": 244875.0,
      "text": "until he was 42 years old,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 244899.0,
      "end_time": 248258.0,
      "text": "and then married Dolley and lived happily ever after for 40 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 248576.0,
      "end_time": 250179.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 250203.0,
      "end_time": 251363.0,
      "text": "To put it bluntly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 251387.0,
      "end_time": 252794.0,
      "text": "Hamilton&#39;s the kind of person"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 252818.0,
      "end_time": 255470.0,
      "text": "about whom you would write a hip-hop musical --"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 255710.0,
      "end_time": 256980.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 256122.0,
      "end_time": 257710.0,
      "text": "and Madison is the kind of person"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 257733.0,
      "end_time": 260138.0,
      "text": "about whom you would not write a hip-hop musical."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 260163.0,
      "end_time": 261183.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 261207.0,
      "end_time": 263207.0,
      "text": "Or indeed, a musical of any kind at all."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 264192.0,
      "end_time": 265361.0,
      "text": "But together,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 265385.0,
      "end_time": 267457.0,
      "text": "they had become a rather unlikely pairing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 267481.0,
      "end_time": 269530.0,
      "text": "and they had produced the Federalist Papers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 269554.0,
      "end_time": 271626.0,
      "text": "which offered a justification"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 271650.0,
      "end_time": 272815.0,
      "text": "and, as I mentioned,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 272839.0,
      "end_time": 275750.0,
      "text": "a marketing plan for the Constitution,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 275990.0,
      "end_time": 278828.0,
      "text": "which had been wildly effective and wildly successful."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 280349.0,
      "end_time": 282119.0,
      "text": "Once the new government was in place,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 282143.0,
      "end_time": 284289.0,
      "text": "Hamilton became Secretary of the Treasury,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 284314.0,
      "end_time": 287400.0,
      "text": "and he had a very specific idea in mind."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 287280.0,
      "end_time": 288181.0,
      "text": "And that was"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 288205.0,
      "end_time": 291176.0,
      "text": "to do for financial institutions and infrastructure"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 291200.0,
      "end_time": 294664.0,
      "text": "exactly what Madison had done for constitutions."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 295485.0,
      "end_time": 297664.0,
      "text": "Again, his contemporaries all knew it."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 297688.0,
      "end_time": 299522.0,
      "text": "One of them told Madison,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 299546.0,
      "end_time": 301299.0,
      "text": "who can&#39;t have liked it very much,"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 301323.0,
      "end_time": 304467.0,
      "text": "that Hamilton was the Newton of infrastructure."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 305214.0,
      "end_time": 307371.0,
      "text": "The idea was pretty straightforward."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 307395.0,
      "end_time": 310960.0,
      "text": "Hamilton would give the United States a national bank,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 310790.0,
      "end_time": 314196.0,
      "text": "a permanent national debt --"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 314220.0,
      "end_time": 316428.0,
      "text": "he said it would be \"immortal,\" his phrase --"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 317487.0,
      "end_time": 323660.0,
      "text": "and a manufacturing policy that would enable trade and manufacturing"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 323900.0,
      "end_time": 324647.0,
      "text": "rather than agriculture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 324672.0,
      "end_time": 328508.0,
      "text": "which was where the country&#39;s primary wealth had historically been."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 329278.0,
      "end_time": 331602.0,
      "text": "Madison went utterly ballistic."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 332424.0,
      "end_time": 335455.0,
      "text": "And in this pivotal, critical decision,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 335479.0,
      "end_time": 339726.0,
      "text": "instead of just telling the world that his old friend Hamilton was wrong"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 339750.0,
      "end_time": 342449.0,
      "text": "and was adopting the wrong policies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 342473.0,
      "end_time": 344235.0,
      "text": "he actually began to argue"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 344259.0,
      "end_time": 347360.0,
      "text": "that Hamilton&#39;s ideas were unconstitutional --"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 347384.0,
      "end_time": 350354.0,
      "text": "that they violated the very nature of the Constitution"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 350378.0,
      "end_time": 352603.0,
      "text": "that the two of them had drafted together."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 354137.0,
      "end_time": 357180.0,
      "text": "Hamilton responded the way you would expect."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 358140.0,
      "end_time": 363750.0,
      "text": "He declared Madison to be his \"personal and political enemy\" --"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 363990.0,
      "end_time": 364644.0,
      "text": "these are his words."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 364668.0,
      "end_time": 368627.0,
      "text": "So these two founders who had been such close friends and such close allies"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 368651.0,
      "end_time": 369893.0,
      "text": "and such partners,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 369917.0,
      "end_time": 372863.0,
      "text": "then began to produce enmity."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 373602.0,
      "end_time": 375849.0,
      "text": "And they did it in the good, old-fashioned way."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 375874.0,
      "end_time": 377720.0,
      "text": "First, they founded political parties."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 377744.0,
      "end_time": 381328.0,
      "text": "Madison created a party originally called the Democratic Republican Party --"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 381352.0,
      "end_time": 382561.0,
      "text": "\"Republican\" for short --"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 382586.0,
      "end_time": 385421.0,
      "text": "and Hamilton created a party called the Federalist Party."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 386313.0,
      "end_time": 389960.0,
      "text": "Those two parties adopted positions on national politics"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 389984.0,
      "end_time": 392700.0,
      "text": "that were extreme and exaggerated."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 392725.0,
      "end_time": 394459.0,
      "text": "To give you a clear example:"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 394483.0,
      "end_time": 396310.0,
      "text": "Madison, who had always believed"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 396550.0,
      "end_time": 399144.0,
      "text": "that the country would have some manufacturing and some trade"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 399168.0,
      "end_time": 400738.0,
      "text": "and some agriculture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 400762.0,
      "end_time": 402970.0,
      "text": "began attacking Hamilton"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 402994.0,
      "end_time": 406368.0,
      "text": "as a kind of tool of the financial markets"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 407192.0,
      "end_time": 412550.0,
      "text": "whom Hamilton himself intended to put in charge of the country."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 412530.0,
      "end_time": 413820.0,
      "text": "That was an overstatement,"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 413844.0,
      "end_time": 415964.0,
      "text": "but it was something Madison came to believe."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 415988.0,
      "end_time": 417857.0,
      "text": "He also attacked city life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 417881.0,
      "end_time": 420686.0,
      "text": "and he said that the coasts were corrupt,"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 420710.0,
      "end_time": 423340.0,
      "text": "and what people needed to do was to look inwards"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 423365.0,
      "end_time": 425780.0,
      "text": "to the center of the country,"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 425102.0,
      "end_time": 428914.0,
      "text": "to farmers, who were the essence of Republican virtue,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 428939.0,
      "end_time": 432271.0,
      "text": "and they should go back to the values that had made American great,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 432815.0,
      "end_time": 435633.0,
      "text": "specifically the values of the Revolution,"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 435657.0,
      "end_time": 438157.0,
      "text": "and those were the values of low taxes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 438182.0,
      "end_time": 439343.0,
      "text": "agriculture"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 439367.0,
      "end_time": 440627.0,
      "text": "and less trade."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 441231.0,
      "end_time": 445908.0,
      "text": "Hamilton responded to this by saying that Madison was na√Øve,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 445932.0,
      "end_time": 448760.0,
      "text": "that he was childish,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 448100.0,
      "end_time": 450541.0,
      "text": "and that his goal was to turn the United States"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 450565.0,
      "end_time": 452360.0,
      "text": "into a primitive autarchy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 452384.0,
      "end_time": 456219.0,
      "text": "self-reliant and completely ineffectual on the global scale."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 456243.0,
      "end_time": 457754.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 457778.0,
      "end_time": 459483.0,
      "text": "They both meant it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 459507.0,
      "end_time": 461862.0,
      "text": "and there was some truth to each of their claims,"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 461886.0,
      "end_time": 466228.0,
      "text": "because each side was grossly exaggerating the views of the other"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 466252.0,
      "end_time": 468980.0,
      "text": "in order to fight their war."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 468722.0,
      "end_time": 470854.0,
      "text": "They founded newspapers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 470879.0,
      "end_time": 472824.0,
      "text": "and so for the first time in US history,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 472848.0,
      "end_time": 477808.0,
      "text": "the news that people received came entirely through the lens"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 477832.0,
      "end_time": 480462.0,
      "text": "of either the Republican or the Federalist party."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 482879.0,
      "end_time": 484283.0,
      "text": "How does this end?"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 485710.0,
      "end_time": 489305.0,
      "text": "Well, as it turned out, the Constitution did its work."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 489759.0,
      "end_time": 492819.0,
      "text": "But it did its work in surprising ways"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 492843.0,
      "end_time": 496946.0,
      "text": "that Madison himself had not fully anticipated."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 498647.0,
      "end_time": 500558.0,
      "text": "First, there was a series of elections."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 501580.0,
      "end_time": 503649.0,
      "text": "And the first two times out of the box,"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 503673.0,
      "end_time": 507514.0,
      "text": "the Federalists destroyed the Republicans."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 508680.0,
      "end_time": 510910.0,
      "text": "Madison was astonished."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 511798.0,
      "end_time": 513477.0,
      "text": "Of course, he blamed the press."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 513501.0,
      "end_time": 515839.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 515864.00000000006,
      "end_time": 518163.00000000006,
      "text": "And in a rather innovative view --"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 518187.0,
      "end_time": 521373.0,
      "text": "Madison never failed to innovate when he thought about anything --"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 521397.00000000006,
      "end_time": 524620.0,
      "text": "he said the reason that the press was so pro-Federalist"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 524860.0,
      "end_time": 527461.0,
      "text": "is that the advertisers were all Federalists,"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 527485.0,
      "end_time": 532212.0,
      "text": "because they were traders on the coasts who got their capital from Britain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 532236.0,
      "end_time": 534199.0,
      "text": "which Federalism was in bed with."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 535616.0,
      "end_time": 537274.0,
      "text": "That was his initial explanation."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 538520.0,
      "end_time": 540100.0,
      "text": "But despite the fact that the Federalists,"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 540124.0,
      "end_time": 541275.0,
      "text": "once in power,"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 541299.0,
      "end_time": 546524.0,
      "text": "actually enacted laws that criminalized criticism of the government --"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 546548.0,
      "end_time": 548421.0,
      "text": "that happened in the United States --"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 549566.0,
      "end_time": 551331.0,
      "text": "nevertheless,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 551355.0,
      "end_time": 553420.0,
      "text": "the Republicans fought back,"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 553660.0,
      "end_time": 556369.0,
      "text": "and Madison began to emphasize the freedom of speech,"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 556393.0,
      "end_time": 558881.0,
      "text": "which he had built into the Bill of Rights,"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 558905.0,
      "end_time": 561400.0,
      "text": "and the capacity of civil society"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 561640.0,
      "end_time": 562430.0,
      "text": "to organize."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 562454.0,
      "end_time": 565750.0,
      "text": "And sure enough, nationally,"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 565100.0,
      "end_time": 569463.0,
      "text": "small local groups -- they were called Democratic-Republican Societies --"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 569487.0,
      "end_time": 574132.0,
      "text": "began to form and protest against Federalist-dominated hegemony."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 574956.0,
      "end_time": 580193.0,
      "text": "Eventually, the Republicans managed to win a national election --"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 580217.0,
      "end_time": 581675.0,
      "text": "that was in 1800."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 582405.0,
      "end_time": 584625.0,
      "text": "Madison became the Secretary of State,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 584649.0,
      "end_time": 587339.0,
      "text": "his friend and mentor Jefferson became president,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 587363.0,
      "end_time": 589585.0,
      "text": "and they actually, over time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 589609.0,
      "end_time": 594640.0,
      "text": "managed to put the Federalists completely out of business."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 594485.0,
      "end_time": 595771.0,
      "text": "That was their goal."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 597646.0,
      "end_time": 599598.0,
      "text": "Now, why did that happen?"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 600488.0,
      "end_time": 604309.0,
      "text": "It happened because in the structure of the Constitution"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 604333.0,
      "end_time": 608930.0,
      "text": "were several features that actually managed faction"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 608117.0,
      "end_time": 610646.0,
      "text": "the way there were supposed to do in the first place."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 610671.0,
      "end_time": 611926.0,
      "text": "What were those?"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 612335.0,
      "end_time": 614611.0,
      "text": "One -- most important of all --"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 614635.0,
      "end_time": 616449.0,
      "text": "the freedom of speech."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 616473.0,
      "end_time": 618630.0,
      "text": "This was an innovative idea at the time."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 618654.0,
      "end_time": 620913.0,
      "text": "Namely, that if you were out of power,"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 620937.0,
      "end_time": 623695.0,
      "text": "you could still say that the government was terrible."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 624780.0,
      "end_time": 625939.0,
      "text": "Two,"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 626710.0,
      "end_time": 628472.0,
      "text": "civil society organization."
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 628871.0,
      "end_time": 632985.0,
      "text": "The capacity to put together private groups, individuals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 633900.0,
      "end_time": 634616.0,
      "text": "political parties and others"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 634640.0,
      "end_time": 637773.0,
      "text": "who would organize to try to bring about fundamental change."
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 639753.0,
      "end_time": 643950.0,
      "text": "Perhaps most significantly was the separation of powers --"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 643974.0,
      "end_time": 646453.0,
      "text": "an extraordinary component of the Constitution."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 646959.0,
      "end_time": 648906.0,
      "text": "The thing about the separation of powers"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 648931.0,
      "end_time": 651405.0,
      "text": "is that it did then and it does now,"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 651429.0,
      "end_time": 654938.0,
      "text": "drive governance to the center."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 655946.0,
      "end_time": 659258.0,
      "text": "You can get elected to office in the United States"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 659282.0,
      "end_time": 661250.0,
      "text": "with help from the periphery,"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 661274.0,
      "end_time": 662554.0,
      "text": "right or left."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 663296.0,
      "end_time": 664556.0,
      "text": "It turns out,"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 664580.0,
      "end_time": 669919.0,
      "text": "you actually can&#39;t govern unless you bring on board the center."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 670800.0,
      "end_time": 674517.0,
      "text": "There are midterm elections that come incredibly fast"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 674542.0,
      "end_time": 676471.0,
      "text": "after a presidency begins."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 677597.0,
      "end_time": 680790.0,
      "text": "Those drive presidents towards the center."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 680988.0,
      "end_time": 685293.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s a structure in which the president, in fact, does not rule"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 685317.0,
      "end_time": 686728.0,
      "text": "or even govern,"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 686752.0,
      "end_time": 690796.0,
      "text": "but can only propose laws which other people have to agree with --"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 691392.0,
      "end_time": 693974.0,
      "text": "another feature that tends to drive presidents"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 693998.0,
      "end_time": 695756.0,
      "text": "who actually want to get things done"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 695780.0,
      "end_time": 696970.0,
      "text": "to the center."
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 697373.0,
      "end_time": 701605.0,
      "text": "And a glance at the newspapers today will reveal to you"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 701629.0,
      "end_time": 705421.0,
      "text": "that these principles are still completely in operation."
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 706171.0,
      "end_time": 708301.0,
      "text": "No matter how a president gets elected,"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 708325.0,
      "end_time": 711103.0,
      "text": "the president cannot get anything done"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 711825.0,
      "end_time": 715511.0,
      "text": "unless the president first of all follows the rules of the Constitution,"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 715535.0,
      "end_time": 716690.0,
      "text": "because if not,"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 716715.0,
      "end_time": 720120.0,
      "text": "the courts will stand up, as indeed has sometimes occurred,"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 720360.0,
      "end_time": 722896.0,
      "text": "not only recently, but in the past, in US history."
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 722920.0,
      "end_time": 724730.0,
      "text": "And furthermore,"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 724970.0,
      "end_time": 725667.0,
      "text": "the president needs people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 725691.0,
      "end_time": 728763.0,
      "text": "elected officials who know they need to win election"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 728787.0,
      "end_time": 730232.0,
      "text": "from centrist voters,"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 730256.0,
      "end_time": 734481.0,
      "text": "also to back his or her policies in order to pass laws."
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 735382.0,
      "end_time": 737957.0,
      "text": "Without it, nothing much happens."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 739685.0,
      "end_time": 743257.0,
      "text": "The takeaway of this brief excursus"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 743281.0,
      "end_time": 747430.0,
      "text": "into the history of partisanship, then, is the following:"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 749318.0,
      "end_time": 750963.0,
      "text": "partisanship is real;"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 751868.0,
      "end_time": 753282.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s profound;"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 753829.0,
      "end_time": 756261.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s extraordinarily powerful,"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 756285.0,
      "end_time": 758740.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s terribly upsetting."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 759315.0,
      "end_time": 765200.0,
      "text": "But the design of the Constitution is greater than partisanship."
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 766980.0,
      "end_time": 770531.0,
      "text": "It enables us to manage partisanship when that&#39;s possible,"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 770555.0,
      "end_time": 776531.0,
      "text": "and it enables us actually to overcome partisan division"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 776555.0,
      "end_time": 778203.0,
      "text": "and produce compromise,"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 778227.0,
      "end_time": 780472.0,
      "text": "when and only when that is possible."
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 782903.0,
      "end_time": 786405.0,
      "text": "A technology like that is a technology that worked"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 786429.0,
      "end_time": 788146.0,
      "text": "for the founders,"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 788170.0,
      "end_time": 790611.0,
      "text": "it worked for their grandchildren,"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 791904.0,
      "end_time": 794112.0,
      "text": "it didn&#39;t work at the moment of the Civil War,"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 794136.0,
      "end_time": 796500.0,
      "text": "but then it started working again."
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 796485.0,
      "end_time": 798786.0,
      "text": "And it worked for our grandparents,"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 798810.0,
      "end_time": 800363.0,
      "text": "our parents,"
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 800388.0,
      "end_time": 803806.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s going to work for us."
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 805288.0,
      "end_time": 809744.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 810545.0,
      "end_time": 812646.0,
      "text": "So what you should do is really simple."
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 813589.0,
      "end_time": 815322.0,
      "text": "Stand up for what you believe in,"
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 816207.0,
      "end_time": 819413.0,
      "text": "support the organizations that you care about,"
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 819437.0,
      "end_time": 822274.0,
      "text": "speak out on the issues that matter to you,"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 823245.0,
      "end_time": 825760.0,
      "text": "get involved,"
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 825100.0,
      "end_time": 826615.0,
      "text": "make change,"
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 826639.0,
      "end_time": 828534.0,
      "text": "express you opinion,"
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 828558.0,
